hook.real_world_problem:
Flipkart product page with REST:

```
Frontend makes 6 API calls per page load:
  GET /api/products/PROD-123               → 2.1KB (need 200 bytes)
  GET /api/products/PROD-123/reviews?limit=3 → 4.8KB (need 800 bytes)
  GET /api/sellers/SELL-456                → 1.2KB (need 100 bytes)
  GET /api/shipping/estimate?product=PROD-123 → 0.9KB (need 50 bytes)
  GET /api/offers/product/PROD-123         → 3.1KB (need 200 bytes)
  GET /api/images/PROD-123?size=thumb      → 0.8KB (need 50 bytes)

Total: 6 round trips, 13KB transferred, 600ms wait
User sees: blank page for 600ms, then all at once

With GraphQL (one query):
  query ProductPage($id: ID!) {
    product(id: $id) {
      name price { amount currency }
      reviews(first: 3) { rating comment }
      seller { name rating }
      shipping { estimatedDays cost }
    }
  }

Result: 1 round trip, 400 bytes, 120ms, zero over-fetching
```

concept_explanation.schema_definition:
**GraphQL Schema Definition Language (SDL):**

```graphql
# Types:
type Product {
  id: ID!            # Non-null ID (! = required)
  name: String!      # Non-null String
  price: Price!      # Nested object type
  description: String  # Nullable String (no !)
  reviews: [Review!]!  # Non-null list of non-null Reviews
  category: Category!  # Enum type
}

type Price {
  amount: Float!
  currency: String!   # 'INR', 'USD'
}

enum Category {
  ELECTRONICS
  CLOTHING
  BOOKS
  HOME_KITCHEN
}

# Input type for mutations (not return types):
input CreateProductInput {
  name: String!
  priceAmount: Float!
  category: Category!
  description: String
}

# Entry points:
type Query {
  product(id: ID!): Product          # returns nullable
  products(category: Category): [Product!]!  # list, always non-null
  searchProducts(keyword: String!): [Product!]!
}

type Mutation {
  createProduct(input: CreateProductInput!): Product!
  updatePrice(productId: ID!, newPrice: Float!): Product!
  deleteProduct(id: ID!): Boolean!
}
```

